By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The Senate is now in a closed-door meeting with the Acting Inspector General of Police, Mohammed Adamu over the ceaseless insecurity In the country. Recall that the senate had last week extended invitation to the IGP to come and brief the members of the red chamber why the insecurity has persisted and the plans he is making the arrest the ugly trend. Sundiata Post recalls that Senators who their turns during plenary last week, condemned the endless insecurity spilling over across the states including Kaduna state which shares common boundary with the nation’s capital, Abuja. The killings in the country by bandits and kidnappings along Kaduna-Abuja road has caused travellers going to Kaduna to resort to travelling by rail and this has increased the transport fair by rail from Abuja to Kaduna from N1,500 to N15,000. Details Later….